HEADWORD: Laborer
<hw>La"bor*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>labourer</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who labors in a toilsome
occupation; a person who does work that requires strength rather than
skill, as distinguished from that of an
<contr>artisan</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laboring</ent>⟦br⟧
